Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Peel and slice the @potatoes{450%g} into 1cm thick rounds. Once boiling, add the potato slices to the water and simmer until just tender, ~{8-12%minutes}.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Once cooked, reserve some of the @reserved potato water{100%ml} in a #bowl{}, then carefully drain in a #colander{}.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Pop the (now empty) potato pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle}. Once hot, add the garlic and @Italian style herbs{1%thyme}. Cook, stirring frequently, for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, reserved potato water and half the grated hard Italian style cheese to the pan. Mix together, bring to the boil, then remove from the heat. Season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Lay the cooked potato slices in layers in an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}, then pour over the creamy sauce. Sprinkle the @mature Cheddar cheese{30%g} on top. Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until golden brown and bubbling, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Put the dish onto a baking sheet to catch any drips.

While the gratin bakes, wrap 2 rashers of @British streaky bacon{4%rashers} around each @British chicken breasts{2}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{2%drizzles} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, lay in the bacon-wrapped chicken and cook until golden and crisp, ~{4-5%minutes} each side. Once browned, pop onto a #baking tray{} and roast on the top shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook bacon thoroughly.

When 10-15 mins of cooking time remain, pop the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g} onto the same tray as the chicken. Drizzle with @oil{1%drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and bake for the remaining time. When the chicken is cooked, remove from your oven, cover with #foil{} and allow it to rest for a couple of mins.

Meanwhile, pop the @BBQ sauce{96%g} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce into the (now empty) chicken pan and return to medium-high heat. Bring to the boil, then simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}, stirring frequently. Remove from the heat.

Once everything is ready, reheat the BBQ sauce if needed. Share the gratin and roasted Tenderstem® between your plates. Slice each chicken breast widthways into roughly 5 pieces and serve alongside with the BBQ sauce spooned on top. Enjoy!